pullRequest.body:
Introduces `flexibleBinders`, which is an extensible system for binder notations that allow destructuring, bounded domains, and other niceties. Integrates this into `notation3`, and makes `Finset.sum`/`Finset.prod` use it.

nodes.body: (@jcommelin This isn't done yet, but I just got to the point of deleting the custom delaborators for bigsum/bigprod and switching them to use `notation3`. You can write stuff like `‚àè x ‚àà s √óÀ¢ t, f x = ‚àè (x ‚àà s) (y ‚àà t), f (x, y)` with it, and you can define your own binders too just by defining a macro; enabling `‚àë i + j = 10, i * j` for the antidiagonal can be done in just a few lines, though it doesn't pretty print that way.)
